generationModele

Class Parameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • generationModele.Parameter

  • public class Parameter
extends java.lang.Object
    A parameter is a parameter defining an norm`

    A parameter consists of :

    • A institutional parameter father on which the parameter is based
    • A name which is assigned at its creation and which is the same than its institutional parameter father.
    • A set of definition which can be continous or discrete and which is constrained by the institutional parameter father
    • A default Value

        Parameter Constructor.
        Parameters:
        borneInf - The lower bound of the set of definition of the parameter. It must be compatible with the institutional parameter father 's one.
        borneSup - The upper bound of the set of definition of the parameter. It must be compatible with the institutional parameter father 's one.
        defaultValue - The default value of the parameter. It must belong to the set of definition.
        fatherParamater - The institutional parameter father on which is built the parameter.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Raise an exception if the defaultValue doesn't belong to the set of definition. Raise an exception if the set of definition is not compatible with the parameter father's one. Raise an exception if the lower bound is superior to the upper bound.
